33/*
34 * Top - a top users display for Unix
35 *
36 * This file defines the default locations on the screen for various parts
37 * of the display. These definitions are used by the routines in "display.c"
38 * for cursor addressing.
39 */
40
41#define X_LASTPID 10
42#define Y_LASTPID 0
43#define X_LASTPIDWIDTH 13
44#define X_LOADAVE 27
45#define Y_LOADAVE 0
46#define X_LOADAVEWIDTH 7
47#define X_MINIBAR 50
48#define Y_MINIBAR 0
49#define X_UPTIME 48
50#define Y_UPTIME 0
51#define X_PROCSTATE 15
52#define Y_PROCSTATE 1
53#define X_BRKDN 15
54#define Y_BRKDN 1
55#define X_CPUSTATES 0
56#define Y_CPUSTATES 2
57#define X_KERNEL 8
58#define Y_KERNEL 3
59#define X_MEM 8
60#define Y_MEM 3
61#define X_SWAP 6
62#define Y_SWAP 4
63#define Y_MESSAGE 4
64#define X_HEADER 0
65#define Y_HEADER 5
66#define X_IDLECURSOR 0
67#define Y_IDLECURSOR 4
68#define Y_PROCS 6
